<p>You can view and copy the source of this page.
</p><textarea readonly="" accesskey="," id="wpTextbox1" cols="80" rows="25" style="" class="mw-editfont-monospace" lang="en" dir="ltr" name="wpTextbox1">&lt;noinclude>
The debug menu allows you to edit almost everything in the game. It is vital for testing and debugging the game, and it can help players who encounter a bug. Of course, using it for other purposes is considered [[Cheating|cheating]], but who cares in a single-player game?

== Debug messages ==
Use the {{key|~}} to toggle debug messages - Will show various debug messages, and will allow you to see things like the age/damage/freshness values of various items, and more!


== Main debug menu ==
&lt;/noinclude>
To enable this menu, you will need to edit the [[Controls]]. Go to the main menu by pressing {{key|Esc}} followed by the keybindings list by pressing {{key|1}}. Close to the bottom of the list will be the Debug Menu which should be in red and unbound. Press {{key|+}} followed by the appropriate letter to assign a key of your choice. Note: many keys are already bound to other features, using the {{key|`}} key is a good option as it's unbound by default{{Verify|Not by keybindings.json...}} and is in the same place as the Debug messages and Console Commands present in many PC games.

{{key|''Unassigned''}} — ''Debug menu.'' Opens up a list and asks you what Debug you want to do.
: {{key|1}}'': Wish for an item.'' — Type ''/hammer'' to search for "hammer", then press {{key|up}} and {{key|down}} to cycle through jackhammer, hammer, sledge hammer, etc. Hitting enter will exit search, hitting enter again will ask for an amount. Entering a value will add that value times the default stack size number of items to inventory. {{key|q}} exits.
: {{key|2}}'': Teleport - Short Range'' — Select a location in sight to move to.
: {{key|3}}'': Teleport - Long Range'' — Asks to what [[map]] square you want to move to, then places you randomly in the selected [[map]] square.
: {{key|4}}'': Reveal map'' - Instantly explores the current overmap.
: {{key|5}}'': Spawn NPC'' - Spawns random NPC nearby.
: {{key|6}}'': Spawn Monster'' — It works the same as item wishing for the most part; pressing {{key|f}} will let you make the monster friendly if you want. After making your selection, move the cursor to pick a location to place the monster. 
: {{key|7}}'': Check game state...'' - Shows game state, planned events, active monsters, active NPCs and locations of these NPCs, and your location.
: {{key|8}}'': Kill NPCs'' - Kills all NPCs
: {{key|9}}'': Mutate'' — Allow to toggle your [[traits]] &amp; [[mutation]]s. If the mutation requires crossing the threshold, you need to first add the threshold mutation.
: {{key|0}}'': Spawn a vehicle'' - Spawn vehicle from the list.
: {{key|a}}'': Change all [[skills]]'' - Allows you to increase and decrease skill values using a menu.
: {{key|b}}'': Learn all melee styles'' - Unlocks all melee styles, including a debug one.
: {{key|c}}'': Unlock all recipes'' - Unlocks all recipes, including unlearnable recipes.
: {{key|d}}'': Edit player/NPC'' - Allows you to edit the player or NPCs. See below for options.
: {{key|e}}'': Spawn [[Artifact]]'' — Creates natural artifact and forms anomaly around it.
: {{key|f}}'': Spawn Clairvoyance [[Artifact]]'' - Adds clairvoyance artifact to inventory, allowing you to see through walls.
: {{key|g}}'': Map Editor'' - Opens [[map]] editor, use {{key|q}} to cancel.
: {{key|h}}'': Change weather'' - Select a new weather to start.
: {{key|i}}'': Kill all monsters'' - Kills all active monsters. Processes their death effect(s) as normal.
: {{key|j}}'': Display [[horde]]s'' - Displays the hordes on the map. Also displays hordes created by [[Fungal bloom|Fungal blooms]], [[Anthill|Anthills]] etc.
: {{key|k}}'': Test Item Group'' - Tests item groups; this submenu is exited by selecting the 'cancel' option.
: {{key|l}}'': Damage self'' - Damages torso with inputted amount. Negative values heal.
: {{key|m}}'': Show Sound Clustering''
: {{key|o}}'': Display weather''
: {{key|p}}'': Display overmap scents'' - Shows player scent values on the overmap.
: {{key|q}}'': Change time'' - Change the current year, season, day, hour, minute, and amount of turns.
: {{key|r}}'': Set automove route'' - Moves player to selected location, by walking normally.
: {{key|m}}'': Show mutation category levels'' - Shows the levels of the various threshold mutations.
: {{key|t}}'': Overmap editor'' - Allows you to edit the overmap. Locations in red will not be changed. Follow on-screen instructions.
: {{key|u}}'': Cancel''

=== Edit player/NPCs ===

Looking at an NPC with this debug feature shows the name, class, destination, internal values (Trust, Fear, Anger, Owed, Aggression, Bravery, Collector, Altruism, and the needs of the NPC.

: {{key|s}}'': Edit skills'': - Allows editing of the NPC, or player skills
: {{key|t}}'': Edit Stats'': - Edit the player or NPC maximum stats.
: {{key|i}}'': Grant items'': - Grants items using the same interface as the main debug menu item grant mechanics.
: {{key|d}}'': Delete all items'': - Deletes all items and clothing on the character.
: {{key|w}}'': Wear/Wield an item from NPC/Player's inventory'': - Selects item to (un)wear/(un)wield.
: {{key|h}}'': Set hit points'': - Set the hitpoints on a bodypart. Can go over and under natural limits.
: {{key|p}}'': Cause pain'': - Enter a number of pain to cause, negative numbers removes pain.
: {{key|a}}'': Set health'': - Allows you to edit the [[health]] values.
: {{key|n}}'': Set needs'': - Allows you to see and edit the [[Hidden_stats#Hunger|Hunger]], [[Hidden_stats#Thirst|Thirst]], [[Hidden_stats#Fatigue|Fatigue]] and [[Hidden_stats#Vitamins|Vitamins]] levels of the NPC/player.
: {{key|u}}'': Mutate'': - Edits mutations/traits of the NPC/player using the same interface as the previous menu.
: {{key|@}}'': Status Window'': Shows the status window. Same window as the normal {{key|@}} would show.
: {{key|e}}'': teleport'': - Performs short range teleport, like debug feature above.
: {{key|m}}'': Add mission'': - NPC ONLY - Adds a possible mission to the NPC. NPC's can have multiple missions, this mission is probably added to the end of the possible mission list.
: {{key|c}}'': Randomize with class'': - NPC ONLY - Select a new NPC class, and randomizes the NPC given this class. Creates new name and items. 
: {{key|q}}'': quit'': - Quits this menu.
</textarea><div class="templatesUsed"><div class="mw-templatesUsedExplanation"><p>Templates used on this page:
